<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4685.1.1>
    bibo:endPage "67" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2019-10-11" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "4685" ;
    dc:creator "Lobato-Vila, Irene; Pujade-Villar, Juli" ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "Revision of world Ceroptresini (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) with the description of a new genus and five new species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772839>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772854>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772872>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772874> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772839>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Female faces of valid species of Ceroptres: a) C. kovalevi (type), discontinuous lines point out vertical carinae; b) C. lanigerae (type); c) C. minutissimi (type); d) C. montensis (type); e) C. petiolicola (type); f) C. pisum (type); g) C. quercusobtusilobae (type); h) C. rufiventris (type); i) C. snellingi (type)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772839/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772854>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. a) Ceroptres snellingi lateral and b) dorsal habitus (type)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772854/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772872>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Ceroptres snellingi (material from Mexico): a) female head in anterior view; b) female head in dorsal view; c) male head in anterior view; d) male head in dorsal view; e) female antenna; f) male antenna (with a detail of the last segments, inset image); g) mesosoma in dorsal view; h) mesosoma in lateral view; i) female metasoma in lateral view; j) tarsal claws; k) propodeum; l) radial cell of the forewing." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772872/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772874>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Some of the galls mentioned in this study: a) an undescribed species of Andricus (ref. 069); b) Sphaeroteras nr pulchripennis (ref. 103); c) Dros perlentum (ref. 123); d) Neuroterus eugeros (ref. 182); e) Andricus georgei (ref. 206); f) unknown leaf gall of Neuroterus (ref. 225); g) unknown leaf spherical gall (ref. 266); h) Andricus sphaericus (ref. 303); i) Andricus sphaericus (ref. 307); j) Andricus group georgei (ref. 312); k) Melikaiella amphibolensis (ref. 338); l) an undescribed species of Andricus on leaves (ref. P015); m) Atrusca sp. (ref. P149); n) unknown (P225); o) unknown undetachable leaf gall (ref. P233); p) unknown gall inside secondary leaf nerves (ref. P307); q) Atrusca pictor (ref. P322); r) Atrusca sp. (ref. P328); s) unknown (ref. 2B10, 13B6); t) unknown, a mix of galls (ref. 2840); u) unknown leaf petiole gall (ref. P366); v) unknown twig gall (ref. P308)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772874/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

